doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head
    title Timestamp Microservice - Nicholas Asimov
    link(href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootswatch/3.3.6/flatly/bootstrap.min.css", rel="stylesheet", integrity="sha384-XYCjB+hFAjSbgf9yKUgbysEjaVLOXhCgATTEBpCqT1R3jvG5LGRAK5ZIyRbH5vpX", crossorigin="anonymous")
  body
    .container
      .test
        h1(style="margin-bottom: 15px;") API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
        p Written by: #[a(href="https://www.freecodecamp.com/nicholasasimov") Nicholas Asimov]
        blockquote
          h3 User stories:
          ol
            li I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
            li If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
            li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
        h3 Example usage:
        code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/December%2015,%202015
        br
        code https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/1450137600
        h4 Example output:
        code { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }
